        <name>23.4.2.2 FS expression 2</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;
Verify that the Fourier series of 
\[ f(t) = \dfrac{ t^2}{4} \hspace{1cm} \pi \leq t \leq \pi \hspace{1cm} f(t + 2\pi) = f(t) \] is
\[ \dfrac{\pi^2}{12} + \sum_{n=1}^\infty \dfrac{\cos n\pi}{n^2} \cos nt \]
and use it to calculate
&lt;ol class="HELM_parts_inline"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;\( 1 + \dfrac{1}{2^2} + \dfrac{1}{3^2} + \dfrac{1}{4^2} + \dots = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;li&gt;\( 1 - \dfrac{1}{2^2} + \dfrac{1}{3^2} - \dfrac{1}{4^2} + \dots  = \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]][[feedback:prt2]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;li&gt;\( 1 + \dfrac{1}{3^2} + \dfrac{1}{5^2} + \dfrac{1}{7^2} + \dots  = \) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]][[feedback:prt3]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>We have the Fourier series
\[ \dfrac{\pi^2}{12} + \sum_{n=1}^\infty \dfrac{\cos n\pi}{n^2} \cos nt \]
&lt;ol class="HELM_parts_inline"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
Now setting \(t = \pi\) we have \(f(t) = \dfrac{\pi^2}{4}\), and therefore
\[ 
\begin{align}
\dfrac{\pi^2}{4} &amp;amp;= \dfrac{\pi^2}{12} +  \sum _{n=1}^\infty \dfrac{\cos n\pi}{n^2} \cos n\pi \\
&amp;amp;=  \dfrac{\pi^2}{12} + 1 + \dfrac{1}{2^2} + \dfrac{1}{3^2} + \dfrac{1}{4^2} + \dots
\end{align}
\]
which can be rearranged to give
\[  1 + \dfrac{1}{2^2} + \dfrac{1}{3^2} + \dfrac{1}{4^2} + \dots = \dfrac{\pi^2}{6} \] &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
Now setting \(t = 0\) we have \(f(t) = 0 \), and therefore
\[ 
\begin{align}
0 &amp;amp;= \dfrac{\pi^2}{12} +  \sum _{n=1}^\infty \dfrac{\cos n\pi}{n^2} \\
&amp;amp;=  \dfrac{\pi^2}{12} - 1 + \dfrac{1}{2^2} - \dfrac{1}{3^2} + \dfrac{1}{4^2} - \dots
\end{align}
\]
which can be rearranged to give
\[  1 - \dfrac{1}{2^2} + \dfrac{1}{3^2} - \dfrac{1}{4^2} + \dots = \dfrac{\pi^2}{12} \] &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
Adding the results from part (a) and (b) together gives
\[ 1 + \dfrac{1}{3^2} + \dfrac{1}{5^2} + \dfrac{1}{7^2} + \dots = \dfrac{\pi^2}{8} \]
&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;</generalfeedback>
